      passage: `<div style='text-align:center;font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin:2px 0'>Land Areas of Five Tribal Nations across the United States</div><table style='border-collapse:collapse;margin:6px auto;font-size:13px'><tr><th style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px'>Tribal nation</th><th style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px'>Location</th><th style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px'>Area (square miles)</th></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Jicarilla Apache Nation</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>New Mexico</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>1,374</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Tohono O&rsquo;odham Nation</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Arizona</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>4,453</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Choctaw Nation</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Oklahoma</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>10,864</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Hopi Tribe</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Arizona</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>2,533</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>Standing Rock Sioux Tribe</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>North and South Dakota</td><td style='border:1px solid var(--border,#d0d0d0);padding:3px 10px;text-align:center'>3,662</td></tr></table><p>A geography student, a member of the Standing Rock Sioux Tribe, sets out to weigh the land his tribal nation holds across North and South Dakota against the land held by several tribal nations elsewhere. Reading the table, he sees that the Standing Rock Sioux Tribe covers 3,662 square miles, whereas the Jicarilla Apache Nation in New Mexico covers _____</p>`,
